[
  {
    "startTime": 0.24,
    "endTime": 1.3,
    "text": "G'day guys."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 1.3,
    "endTime": 3.129,
    "text": "Welcome to this episode of Aussie English."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 3.129,
    "endTime": 7.609,
    "text": "Today I want to talk to you about 1 simple\r\ntrick to sound more like an Aussie when you"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 7.609,
    "endTime": 8.96,
    "text": "speak English."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 8.96,
    "endTime": 10.120000000000001,
    "text": "Let's go."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 15.14,
    "endTime": 27.279,
    "text": "So, this one simple trick is words that end\r\nwith -er, -or, -ar, -ure, -our, and -a (and -re*),"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 27.279,
    "endTime": 31.599,
    "text": "all have the same pronunciation in\r\nAustralian English, at least the majority"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 31.599,
    "endTime": 32.89,
    "text": "of the time."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 32.89,
    "endTime": 35.54,
    "text": "And this is the short /ɑ/ sound."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 35.54,
    "endTime": 41.73,
    "text": "So, we make this sound by just lowering our\r\njaw, quite a way, and literally just saying"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 41.73,
    "endTime": 47.44,
    "text": "the sound /ɑ:/, but short, /ɑ/."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 47.44,
    "endTime": 54.57,
    "text": "So, as opposed to words like \"bar\" and \"car\",\r\nwhich have the long ɑ sound, this sound is"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 54.57,
    "endTime": 56.980000000000004,
    "text": "a very short sound."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 56.98,
    "endTime": 59.779999999999994,
    "text": "/ɑ/."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 59.78,
    "endTime": 65.56,
    "text": "So, let's go through a couple of words for\r\neach one of these endings so you can practice"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 65.56,
    "endTime": 68.39,
    "text": "sounding more like an Aussie."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 68.39,
    "endTime": 71.27,
    "text": "And I will admit there are exceptions."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 71.27,
    "endTime": 76.17,
    "text": "Like everything in English, the rule is that\r\nthere is always an exception."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 76.17,
    "endTime": 81.799,
    "text": "But, the majority of the time these words\r\nare going to end with the sound /ɑ/."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 81.8,
    "endTime": 83.72,
    "text": "So it's a good place to start."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 87.32,
    "endTime": 90.63999999999999,
    "text": "So, words that end with -a."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 90.64,
    "endTime": 94.319,
    "text": "Area"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 94.319,
    "endTime": 97.74900000000001,
    "text": "Cobra"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 97.749,
    "endTime": 101.219,
    "text": "Coma"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 101.219,
    "endTime": 105.65899999999999,
    "text": "Flora"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 105.659,
    "endTime": 107.63000000000001,
    "text": "Words that end with -ar."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 107.63,
    "endTime": 111.21,
    "text": "Polar"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 111.21,
    "endTime": 115.02999999999999,
    "text": "Cheddar"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 115.03,
    "endTime": 118.27,
    "text": "Linear"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 118.27,
    "endTime": 122.74,
    "text": "Jaguar"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 122.74,
    "endTime": 125.219,
    "text": "Words that end with -er."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 125.219,
    "endTime": 128.64,
    "text": "Water"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 128.64,
    "endTime": 132.0,
    "text": "Laser"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 132.0,
    "endTime": 135.4,
    "text": "Maker"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 135.4,
    "endTime": 139.76000000000002,
    "text": "Beer"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 139.76,
    "endTime": 142.94,
    "text": "Words that end with -re."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 142.94,
    "endTime": 145.85999999999999,
    "text": "Centre"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 145.88,
    "endTime": 149.14,
    "text": "Theatre"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 149.14,
    "endTime": 152.77999999999997,
    "text": "Tyre"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 152.78,
    "endTime": 157.4,
    "text": "Fire"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 157.4,
    "endTime": 160.02,
    "text": "Words that end with -or."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 160.02,
    "endTime": 163.34,
    "text": "Mirror"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 163.34,
    "endTime": 166.84,
    "text": "Actor"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 166.84,
    "endTime": 170.28,
    "text": "Alligator"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 170.28,
    "endTime": 174.98,
    "text": "Doctor"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 174.98,
    "endTime": 178.0,
    "text": "Words that end with -ure."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 178.01,
    "endTime": 181.26,
    "text": "Treasure"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 181.26,
    "endTime": 185.01,
    "text": "Cure"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 185.01,
    "endTime": 188.23,
    "text": "Nature"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 188.23,
    "endTime": 192.39999999999998,
    "text": "Structure"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 192.4,
    "endTime": 195.6,
    "text": "Words that end with -our."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 195.6,
    "endTime": 199.06,
    "text": "Favour"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 199.06,
    "endTime": 202.22,
    "text": "Neighbour"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 202.22,
    "endTime": 205.9,
    "text": "Humour"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 205.9,
    "endTime": 210.14000000000001,
    "text": "Hour"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 210.14,
    "endTime": 216.551,
    "text": "And then, as a little bonus here at the end,\r\nguys, sometimes words with -ur at the end"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 216.551,
    "endTime": 218.72,
    "text": "are pronounced as /ɑ/ as well."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 218.72,
    "endTime": 222.83,
    "text": "Although, a lot of the time they're going\r\nto sound like /ɜ/."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 222.83,
    "endTime": 226.57000000000002,
    "text": "And one example I could think of was \"amateur\"."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 226.57,
    "endTime": 230.04999999999998,
    "text": "So, that's it for this episode guys."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 230.05,
    "endTime": 236.04000000000002,
    "text": "I really recommend trying to make these pronunciation\r\nchanges IF you want to sound like an Australian."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 236.04,
    "endTime": 241.72,
    "text": "Otherwise, you're going to have somewhat of\r\nan American accent if you're pronouncing that"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 241.72,
    "endTime": 250.72,
    "text": "/r/ sound at the ends of words like \"water\",\r\n\"anchor\", \"treasure\", \"neighbour\"."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 250.72,
    "endTime": 254.12,
    "text": "That is a very American sound with that /r/\r\nsound."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 254.13,
    "endTime": 258.59,
    "text": "In Australian English we don't curl the tongue\r\nup to make the /r/ sound."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 258.59,
    "endTime": 262.19899999999996,
    "text": "We drop the jaw and we keep our tongue flat."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 262.199,
    "endTime": 263.33,
    "text": "/ɑ/"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 263.33,
    "endTime": 267.87,
    "text": "\"Neighbour\", \"treasure\", \"hour\", \"actor\"."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 267.87,
    "endTime": 270.389,
    "text": "Anyway, good luck guys."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 270.389,
    "endTime": 271.389,
    "text": "Keep at it."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 271.389,
    "endTime": 273.84000000000003,
    "text": "Keep improving your Aussie English, and I'll chat to you soon."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 273.84,
    "endTime": 275.44,
    "text": "Peace out. All the best!"
  }
]